Instruction: With the battery installed and all control‑module switches ON, measure the DC voltage between the two cables entering the load module. If ~12 V is present there, then (with power removed) test continuity from the load module input 12 V line through the series diode to the two lamps, and separately test continuity of each lamp filament. This will determine whether the problem is loss of supply to the load module, an open diode, or failed lamps.
