Instruction: With the battery installed and all switches ON, measure the DC voltage between the two cables on the input side and then on the output side of each control module from 2 through 8, one module at a time. Identify the first module in the chain whose output pair does NOT show ~12 V when its input pair does, indicating where the series path to the load is interrupted or miswired.
